<p>
  Involving accessibility early in design reduces rework and improves outcomes for all users. We review wireframes, prototypes, and design specifications to identify potential barriers before development begins.
</p>

<h2>What we review</h2>
<ul class="list-disc mb-300">
  <li class="mb-75">Low- and high-fidelity wireframes</li>
  <li class="mb-75">Interactive prototypes (Figma, Adobe XD, or other tools)</li>
  <li class="mb-75">Design systems and component libraries</li>
  <li>Content structure, hierarchy, and plain language</li>
</ul>

<h2>What to expect</h2>
<p>
  We provide written feedback with specific, actionable recommendations. For more complex work, we can meet with your team directly to walk through findings and discuss solutions together.
</p>

<h2>Request a consultation</h2>
<p>
  Contact us at <a href="mailto:aaact-aatia@ssc-spc.gc.ca">aaact-aatia@ssc-spc.gc.ca</a> to schedule a design review. Share your design files or a prototype link ahead of time so we can prepare.
</p>

